BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:EJm4dbysMCrLrq3ef0skb
SUMMARY:IMPROV 100 TUESDAYS - Intro to Improv: Say Yes!\\\, SPRING'26
DTSTAMP:20260325T021327Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260604T180000
DESCRIPTION:Say yes! Learn to listen\\\, connect\\\, play and use your own 
	life to create stories with others! An 8 week intro to improvised theatre!
	\\n\\n\\n\\nDiscover Unexpected Productions’ philosophy of improvisation\\
	\, developed over our 43 years of improvising in Seattle! \\nYou’ll learn 
	how to actively listen\\\, to use your own life to create collaborative st
	ories\\\, and you’ll work on the fundamental principles of improvisation: 
	what it means to say\\\, “Yes\\\, And”\\\, how to tell stories that includ
	e everyone in the room\\\, how to stop worrying about failing\\\, and the 
	games and concepts behind what we do on stages around the world! \\nUnder 
	the guidance of one of our best Seattle improv teachers\\\, you will learn
	 to:· \\n\\nBe a Better Listener\\nConquer Fears\\nSpark Creativity\\nMeet
	 New People & Make New Friends\\nBecome a Better Problem Solver\\nGain Con
	fidence·\\nFail With Grace (and Maybe Even Enjoy It)\\nSay Yes More in You
	r Life\\nGet Out of Your Comfort Zone\\nBecome a Better Public Speaker\\nD
	iscover More About Yourself\\n…and have a blast doing it!\\n\\nTime and Da
	tes: Tuesdays for eight (8) weeks\\\, from March 24 to May 22\\\, 7pm to 9
	:30pm \\nNOTE: Attendance at the first session of your course is mandatory
	 as it sets the agenda for the entire quarter. If you think you will have 
	to miss the first class\\\, please consider registering for the next quart
	er. \\nNo Prerequisites. All students begin at this level\\\, even those w
	ith existing improv experience. It’s a prerequisite to the other levels. \
	\nLocation: 5700 6th Ave St\\\, Suite 109\\\, Umbrella Room\\\, Seattle\\\
	, WA 98108 (In Georgetown\\\, south of downtown\\\, with plenty of parking
	.) \\nMaximum Students: 16 \\nCost: Ticket price $295.00 \\nAge: 18 and ab
	ove \\n**Cancellation policy: If you must cancel before the first class\\\
	, we can only offer credit towards the same level class next quarter. We a
	re unable to offer refunds. If you cancel after the first class we cannot 
	offer credit towards a future class. Again\\\, we are unable to offer refu
	nds.\n\nhttps://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/improv-100-tuesdays-in
	tro-to-improv-build-confidence-spring-26/\n\nFrom Unexpected Productions
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/improv-100-tuesdays-intro-t
	o-improv-build-confidence-spring-26/
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions Improv School ISSAQUAH/EASTSIDE\\\, 1315 NW
	 Mall Street\\\, Suite 4\\\, Issaquah\\\, WA\\\, 98108\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:unexpected-productions
CATEGORIES:Unexpected Productions
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:gCnG572F1XLtQdE8CKVlf
SUMMARY:Ribbon Cutting Celebration: Issaquah Improv School & Clown Garage
DTSTAMP:20260325T021327Z
DTSTART:20260325T110000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us as we officially welcome the Unexpected Productions Imp
	rov School and Clown Garage to Issaquah! On Wednesday\\\, March 25\\\, at 
	11:00 AM\\\, Mayor Mark Mullet will lead a ceremonial ribbon-cutting to ma
	rk the opening of this exciting new creative space dedicated to laughter\\
	\, play\\\, and fearless creativity.\\nPresented in partnership with the I
	ssaquah Chamber of Commerce\\\, this event celebrates the launch of a new 
	hub for training in improv\\\, clown\\\, and physical comedy on the Eastsi
	de. The school will offer classes\\\, workshops\\\, and performances desig
	ned to build confidence\\\, creativity\\\, communication skills\\\, and co
	mmunity.\\nAfter the ribbon-cutting\\\, stay to celebrate with light refre
	shments\\\, conversation\\\, and a chance to explore the new space\\\, mee
	t instructors\\\, and learn more about upcoming classes and programs.\\nWh
	ether you’re an artist\\\, educator\\\, student\\\, or simply curious abou
	t improv\\\, we invite you to come celebrate this exciting new chapter for
	 the Issaquah arts community.\\nCome meet your neighbors\\\, take a look i
	nside\\\, and help us cut the ribbon on a new home for creativity in Issaq
	uah.\n\nhttps://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/ribbon-cutting-celebra
	tion-issaquah-improv-school-clown-garage/\n\nFrom Unexpected Productions
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/ribbon-cutting-celebration-
	issaquah-improv-school-clown-garage/
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions Improv School ISSAQUAH/EASTSIDE\\\, 1315 NW
	 Mall Street\\\, Suite 4\\\, Issaquah\\\, WA\\\, 98108\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:unexpected-productions
CATEGORIES:Unexpected Productions
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:scZUNFjns-yODWpnTcRRC
SUMMARY:The Original Food and Culture Tour of Pike Place Market
DTSTAMP:20260325T021327Z
DTSTART:20260325T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:VOTED 10 BEST FOOD TOURS IN THE COUNTRY BY USA TODAY! Join Savo
	r Seattle for Seattle’s original food and cultural tour of Pike Place Mark
	et! On their signature tour\, they will take you on a journey through the 
	lively and bustling days in the heart of Seattle: Pike Place Market. While
	 their guides give you the most delicious tastings at eight different part
	ners. You’ll also learn the history of the Market and hear the stories of 
	the small-batch food and craft producers that make this place one of Seatt
	le’s most beloved landmarks. Find out why fish fly\, why a pig is our masc
	ot\, how the “Original” Starbucks was founded\, how an alleyway became cov
	ered in gum\, what made Pike Place Market one of Anthony Bourdain’s favori
	te places\, and many more pieces of info Seattle Savor guides we’ll be thr
	illed to share with you while you savor culinary offerings. Once you’re do
	ne\, you’ll be equipped and ready to dive deeper into the historic neighbo
	rhood. Tours are available daily\, starting at 10am and 2\n\nhttps://www.p
	ikeplacemarket.org/events-calendar/the-original-food-and-culture-tour-of-p
	ike-place-market/?occurrence=2026-03-25\n\nFrom Pike Place Market Events
URL:https://www.pikeplacemarket.org/events-calendar/the-original-food-and-c
	ulture-tour-of-pike-place-market/?occurrence=2026-03-25
LOCATION:Pike Place Market
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:events
CATEGORIES:Pike Place Market Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
